******COMMANDS USED FOR THE DOCKER PROJECT*****

ls - Lists files in the current directory.

cd github - Changes to the github directory.

ls - Lists files in the github directory.

cd simple-django-app - Changes to the simple-django-app directory.

ls - Lists files in the simple-django-app directory

docker ps - Displays running Docker containers.

vim Dockerfile - Opens the Dockerfile for editing.

docker build -t counter-app . - Builds the Docker image counter-app from the Dockerfile in the current directory.

docker ps - Displays running Docker containers after build.

docker kill 0d868dc3ba52 && docker rm 0d868dc3ba52 - Stops and removes the container with ID 0d868dc3ba52.

docker run -d -p 8000:8000 counter-app:latest - Runs the counter-app container in detached mode, mapping port 8000 of the container to port 8000 on the host.

ls - Lists files in the current directory. 13-21. cd commands - Navigate through different directories to work on project files.

docker build -t counter-app . - Builds the Docker image again after changes.

docker ps - Displays running Docker containers again.

docker kill c6e654964983 && docker rm c6e654964983 - Stops and removes the container with ID c6e654964983.

docker run -d -p 8000:8000 counter-app:latest - Runs the Docker container again.

cat Dockerfile - Displays the contents of the Dockerfile.

history - Shows the command history.
